1
00:00:05,040 --> 00:00:07,510
Son of Kunja Babu say,

2
00:00:07,523 --> 00:00:10,763
his idea of the spiritual world was

3
00:00:10,763 --> 00:00:14,716
‘swimming in a swimming pool 
full of rasgullas’.

4
00:00:14,766 --> 00:00:18,309
[Slaves of Sweetness | Love vs. Democracy]

5
00:00:18,539 --> 00:00:19,773
That he’d be swimming,

6
00:00:19,773 --> 00:00:22,108
and one would come
into his mouth,

7
00:00:22,108 --> 00:00:23,653
and he’d dive 
and eat an other one,

8
00:00:23,653 --> 00:00:26,653
come up and eat 
a couple of them, and then …

9
00:00:26,653 --> 00:00:29,517
That was his idea 
of the spiritual world:

10
00:00:29,517 --> 00:00:33,295
‘swimming in an ocean of … 
in a swimming pool of sweet balls’.

11
00:00:33,295 --> 00:00:34,483
[Laughing]

12
00:00:34,483 --> 00:00:38,301
I mean, it’s good work, 
if you can get it.

13
00:00:38,521 --> 00:00:43,521
And it’s a pretty sweet concept,

14
00:00:45,138 --> 00:00:48,678
but that’s not

15
00:00:50,766 --> 00:00:52,089
the way.

16
00:00:52,099 --> 00:00:53,305
Because Guru Maharāj 
was saying, 
 

17
00:00:53,305 --> 00:00:58,850
“Kṛṣṇa is not a sweet ball
to be devoured like that.”

18
00:00:58,850 --> 00:01:00,730
He is bhāva-grāhī Janārdana,

19
00:01:00,733 --> 00:01:02,740
He is a bhāv-eater.

20
00:01:02,740 --> 00:01:05,560
He is the Devourer, 
He is the Consumer,

21
00:01:05,578 --> 00:01:08,739
He is the Exploiter.

22
00:01:09,079 --> 00:01:13,301
That man would let 
that little girl exploit him

23
00:01:13,301 --> 00:01:16,266
and say,
“Тhat’s his happiness in life”,

24
00:01:16,266 --> 00:01:19,843
Like every grandmother 
and grandfather—

25
00:01:19,843 --> 00:01:26,603
they are happy dancing slaves 
of their grandchildren.

26
00:01:26,913 --> 00:01:29,113
I am not finding fault with that,

27
00:01:29,113 --> 00:01:31,493
I am using that as a springboard

28
00:01:31,493 --> 00:01:36,293
to help you understand,
then what is Kṛṣṇa conception.

29
00:01:36,296 --> 00:01:43,371
Is it the ultimate degradation
of human beings to be slaves?

30
00:01:43,371 --> 00:01:45,791
‘Dasi’ means ‘slave girl’,

31
00:01:45,791 --> 00:01:50,381
I looked it up 
at the Monier Monier-Williams Dictionary.

32
00:01:50,734 --> 00:01:52,654
Das means ‘slave’,

33
00:01:52,654 --> 00:01:55,284
dasi means ‘slave girl’.”

34
00:01:55,474 --> 00:02:00,834
It’s a great screen name—
‘Slave girl’!

35
00:02:01,424 --> 00:02:04,999
So you’re willing to be a slave 
of someone in this world

36
00:02:04,999 --> 00:02:07,389
because, “Oh, we’re in love,
that’s different.”

37
00:02:07,389 --> 00:02:12,553
—Oh, I see, when you’re in love,
it’s different. Oh, forgot that.

38
00:02:13,279 --> 00:02:14,743
Yea.

39
00:02:14,743 --> 00:02:16,710
So if you are in love with God,
is it different?

40
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:19,297
“No then, I mean that’s 
just humiliating that.”

41
00:02:19,297 --> 00:02:20,524
Wait … so you mean,

42
00:02:20,524 --> 00:02:23,653
you can happily 
be a happy dancing slave

43
00:02:23,653 --> 00:02:27,205
of little four-year-old girl
or sixteen-year-old girl,

44
00:02:27,205 --> 00:02:30,255
or whatever,
and that’s cool.

45
00:02:30,255 --> 00:02:34,066
But to be the happy dancing slave 
of the Ultimate Reality

46
00:02:34,066 --> 00:02:41,297
that’s just … uhhh, 
‘get medieval on ya’.

47
00:02:43,438 --> 00:02:46,500
“We’ve moved 
beyond that as a civilization,

48
00:02:46,500 --> 00:02:50,211
we have democracy now 
like in Washington.”

49
00:02:50,473 --> 00:02:54,153
—Oh, I didn’t get the memo.

